# Force LF line endings for shell scripts and Dockerfiles. Without
# this attribute a Windows host with the default ``core.autocrlf=true``
# rewrites the working-copy to CRLF on checkout, which makes
# ``#!/usr/bin/env bash\r`` an unresolvable shebang the moment the
# script reaches a Linux runner (the container in ``run_all.sh``, the
# CI matrix). LF is the only line-ending that round-trips safely.
*.sh        text eol=lf
Dockerfile* text eol=lf
